Russian Equity Movers: Lukoil, Mostotrest, Polymetal in Moscow

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-26T15:36:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/russian-equity-movers-lukoil-mostotrest-are-active-in-moscow.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rallied
1.5 percent to 1,346.86 by the close in Moscow, erasing an
earlier loss of as much as 3.6 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,315.25 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX),  Russia ’s second-biggest oil producer,
jumped the most in four weeks, adding 2.9 percent to 1,583.5
rubles. Brent erased losses of as much as 2.2 percent and traded
little changed at $103.98 on the London-based ICE Futures Europe
exchange.  OAO  Mostotrest (MSTT)  , the bridge and road builder part-
owned by Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin ’s judo partner Arkady
Rotenberg, gained the most in three weeks after posting an 86
percent jump in first-half profit. The shares gained 2.3 percent
to 157.49 rubles, the biggest gain since Sept. 2.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), the Russian silver and gold
producer, plunged to its lowest in over a month as both metals
tumbled. Its shares slid as much as 9.2 percent before closing
4.1 percent lower at 538.4 rubles, the lowest since Aug. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
